1
00:00:02,030 --> 00:00:03,740
I feel it...

2
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:09,920
An evil spirit is approaching,
filled with anger.

3
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:11,620
An evil spirit?

4
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:13,930
Hakamada's assistant:
Nonomura Kanae

5
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:13,250
What is that?

6
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:23,730
What? Are you talking about Misato-san?

7
00:00:21,430 --> 00:00:25,000
Editor at Tokiwa Publishing:
Tabata Misato

8
00:00:24,460 --> 00:00:26,770
Kanae-san, sorry I'm late.

9
00:00:26,770 --> 00:00:29,970
She's not angry at all.

10
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:32,810
Cafe waitress:
Mizutani Sara

11
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:32,810
No, I am never wrong.

12
00:00:32,810 --> 00:00:35,850
As far as I know, you've always
gotten our orders wrong.

13
00:00:36,850 --> 00:00:40,120
I brought someone who wants
to meet you, Kanae-san.

14
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,420
Oh? Who's that?

15
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:45,750
She's chief editor of our company's
restauranteur magazine, Gourmet-Goo...

16
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:47,810
My name is Yukawa Natsuko.

17
00:00:45,820 --> 00:00:48,590
This episode's client:
Yukawa Natsuko

18
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:50,840
She's the one filled with anger...

19
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:51,220
What?

20
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:53,600
Are you Nonomura-sensei,
the manga illustrator?

21
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,470
Yes...

22
00:00:54,470 --> 00:00:56,330
What can I do for you?

23
00:00:56,330 --> 00:01:00,360
I want to meet the actual protagonist
of the manga, the lawyer.

24
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,370
What?

25
00:01:01,910 --> 00:01:03,840
Hakamada Law Office

26
00:01:02,450 --> 00:01:06,740
I'm chief editor of Tokiwa publishing's
Gourmet-Goo, Yukawa Natsuko.

27
00:01:06,740 --> 00:01:08,230
I'm Hakamada, attorney at law.

28
00:01:06,740 --> 00:01:09,350
Attorney:
Hakamada Yukio

29
00:01:08,230 --> 00:01:09,350
Please come in.

30
00:01:09,350 --> 00:01:12,130
I'm an avid reader of
Nonomura-sensei's manga.

31
00:01:12,130 --> 00:01:15,200
I'm always impressed by
the gallant way the lawyer

32
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,350
sues for compensation, so this
time, I want a consultation.

33
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:21,990
Sensei is only a model
for that protagonist.

34
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:24,290
So, what can I do for you?

35
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:29,010
I want to report them.

36
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,900
Number one in matchmaking

37
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:30,610
"Get-Marriage"?

38
00:01:30,610 --> 00:01:32,060
It's a marriage consultation firm.

39
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:36,340
I'm a registered in the 40,000 yen
per month premium member course.

40
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:38,240
40,000? Expensive.

41
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:38,610
Temp:
Shinozuka Rina

42
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,980
It's been ten months since I enrolled.

43
00:01:39,980 --> 00:01:43,550
At the end of every week, Get-Marriage
hosts a marriage interview party.

44
00:01:43,550 --> 00:01:45,390
I've attended every one,

45
00:01:45,390 --> 00:01:47,180
and have had over fifty
interviews with potential partners.

46
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,520
Fifty times?

47
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:52,020
But, I haven't found a single
marriage prospect yet!

48
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,420
I see...

49
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:58,720
I have never neglected
my womanly endeavors.

50
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,170
I'm conscientious about
beauty and fashion,

51
00:02:01,170 --> 00:02:04,500
my income is higher than men of my age,

52
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:07,050
and yet I can't find a man to marry.

53
00:02:07,050 --> 00:02:09,300
That's because this marriage
consultation firm is incompetent!

54
00:02:12,710 --> 00:02:14,340
Therefore...

55
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:17,790
I want to sue them for all
membership dues I've paid,

56
00:02:17,790 --> 00:02:19,350
and for compensation.

57
00:02:19,350 --> 00:02:21,850
That's just a minor complaint—

58
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:27,320
Do you have the
membership contract form?

59
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,240
Yes.

60
00:02:29,380 --> 00:02:30,720
Right here.

61
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:32,990
Membership Contract Form

62
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:40,270
Based on what I see here,
we might have difficulty.

63
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,740
Why is that?

64
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:45,080
It says here in the clause that
there will be no refund in the event

65
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:48,340
a marriage partner is not found.

66
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,940
We don't have a claim to make.

67
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,000
Claim?

68
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,070
Are you saying I'm just making a claim?

69
00:02:55,070 --> 00:02:57,250
Well, no...

70
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,600
Sensei, you're no different from them.

71
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,910
Huh?

72
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:05,340
I spoke to the representative of
Get-Marriage concerning my situation.

73
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:08,170
This is not the fault of our services.

74
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,830
Get-Marriage representative:
Ozaki Masashi

75
00:03:09,490 --> 00:03:11,570
But, if you want to lay blame...

76
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:19,440
Sensei, you're also saying it's my fault
that I can't find a partner, right?

77
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,270
Um... Not at all.

78
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:26,400
I want to meet a man, fall
in love, and get married.

79
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:29,750
But I'm no beauty, so my
chances are slim.

80
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,550
I have no choice but to rely on
a marriage consultation firm.

81
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:36,080
But, those people take
advantage of our weaknesses,

82
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,070
and rake in membership fees.

83
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:39,730
Well, yes, um...

84
00:03:39,730 --> 00:03:40,590
Sensei.

85
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:43,130
Let's take on this case.

86
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,330
Kurumi-san. When did you get here?

87
00:03:47,330 --> 00:03:50,820
A marriage consultation firm
like this ought to be punished.

88
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:52,410
Who are you?

89
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:55,520
I am a freelance investigator,
Umemoto Kurumi.

90
00:03:56,870 --> 00:04:00,310
Freelance investigator:
Umemoto Kurumi

91
00:03:57,180 --> 00:04:00,680
I will accept your request to
investigate, for a discounted fee.

92
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,250
Thank you!

93
00:04:02,690 --> 00:04:06,650
However, seeing as they
do have this clause...

94
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,150
This case will be difficult.

95
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:12,730
We would have to prove that the
marriage consultation firm

96
00:04:12,730 --> 00:04:15,810
is purposefully preventing
you from finding a partner.

97
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:18,090
Which means what?

98
00:04:18,090 --> 00:04:20,770
That their scheme is to keep
billing for membership

99
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,290
while setting up its members
with mismatched partners.

100
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:27,870
Or, perhaps the matched
partners are hired fakes.

101
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:31,090
I can easily find evidence.

102
00:04:31,090 --> 00:04:33,440
Sensei, will you take this client on?

103
00:04:34,530 --> 00:04:38,000
No, my specialty is divorce.

104
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,450
I have no experience in compensation
lawsuits against corporations.

105
00:04:41,450 --> 00:04:43,090
Don't say that.

106
00:04:43,090 --> 00:04:46,090
Sensei, your specialty in the past
was corporate law, wasn't it?

107
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:47,760
What, is that so?

108
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,340
Well, concerning that...

109
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,440
He was quite outstanding,

110
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:54,340
he fought tooth and nail
against corporations.

111
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,600
Wow.

112
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,600
Then what's the problem, Sensei?

113
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,590
Please.

114
00:04:58,590 --> 00:05:00,390
I will pay you handsomely.

115
00:05:00,370 --> 00:05:03,400
Office landlord:
Toyama Yoshie

116
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:03,640
You don't have anything else to
do anyway, do you, Sensei?

117
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:08,830
I will go all out on this one!

118
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:11,240
You don't have to display
your enthusiasm.

119
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,270
You really don't.

120
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:13,950
No, I want to.

121
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:23,780
Divorce Chaser
~Let's Turn Your Tears into Money~

122
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:28,960
Divorce Chaser Episode 7
Infiltrate the Suspicious Marriage Consultation Firm!

123
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,520
Let me know what day you're going
to the marriage consultation firm.

124
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,700
I'll be going with you.

125
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:40,790
Kurumi-chan is all fired up.

126
00:05:40,790 --> 00:05:42,350
You're right.

127
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:45,950
I've never seen her so insistent
about a client before.

128
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:48,880
I understand how she feels, sort of.

129
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,910
Meaning?

130
00:05:50,910 --> 00:05:52,120
Look at this.

131
00:05:53,660 --> 00:05:55,140
Who's this?

132
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:57,420
That's Kurumi-chan. From four years ago.

133
00:05:58,410 --> 00:05:59,660
What?

134
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:02,790
Before she became an investigator,

135
00:06:02,730 --> 00:06:06,230
4 years ago

136
00:06:02,790 --> 00:06:06,000
she was a regular salaried
employee of a commerce company.

137
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,070
Kurumi!

138
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:10,570
Umemoto Kurumi (4 years ago)

139
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:10,700
Oh, Yohei! Are you done, too?

140
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,970
Yeah, let's go home together.

141
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:15,360
She had a lover who worked
at the same company.

142
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,010
They were virtually living together,

143
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:20,110
and were even discussing marriage.

144
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,950
But...

145
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:24,020
You're being transferred
to the Osaka branch?

146
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:25,930
For how long?

147
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:29,060
The company says for six months.

148
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,670
Six months...

149
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:33,580
This is a good opportunity for me.

150
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:36,570
But, I'm making a promise.

151
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,230
What?

152
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:42,220
When I come back to Tokyo,

153
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:43,560
let's get married.

154
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:45,990
Yohei...

155
00:06:47,270 --> 00:06:51,900
That's how their six-month
long-distance relationship started.

156
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:55,280
Hello, Yohei?

157
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,440
Today's your birthday, isn't it?

158
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:59,770
Sorry, I'm still at work.

159
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:08,520
Kurumi-chan doesn't act like it,
but she doesn't like being alone.

160
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:12,900
I think the stress of the long-distance
relationship took a toll on her.

161
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:16,230
We cannot answer your call right now.

162
00:07:16,230 --> 00:07:19,810
Please leave a message at the beep.

163
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:37,620
Kurumi, I'm home.

164
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:37,620
Six months later

165
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:41,760
Yohei! Welcome home!

166
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:45,010
Who are you?

167
00:07:45,010 --> 00:07:47,850
What do you mean? It's me, Kurumi.

168
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,770
The marriage is off.

169
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:50,990
Huh?

170
00:07:50,990 --> 00:07:53,210
You said we'd get married
when you came back to Tokyo.

171
00:07:53,210 --> 00:07:55,400
Look at your body.
How can you speak of marriage?

172
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:57,380
Have you looked in the mirror lately?

173
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,060
Give the ring back.

174
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:59,150
Hey, what are you doing?

175
00:07:59,150 --> 00:07:59,690
Give it.

176
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:01,800
Stop it! Ow, that hurts!

177
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:07,890
It was quite the shock to her.

178
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,910
Someone who was once so kind to her

179
00:08:15,910 --> 00:08:20,570
changed completely just because
her appearance changed.

180
00:08:20,930 --> 00:08:22,430
I see.

181
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,100
Right.

182
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:30,750
She can't forgive people who disparage
other people's appearances.

183
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:39,890
I'm the representative of
Get-Marriage, Ozaki.

184
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:43,020
I'm Yukawa-sama's assistant, Tachibana.

185
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:43,020
Natsuko's assistant:
Tachibana Tetsu

186
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:45,180
I'm Hakamada, attorney at law.

187
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:46,660
Please, have a seat.

188
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:50,560
Well, this is quite a surprise.

189
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,790
You even hired an attorney.

190
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,230
Of course.

191
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:58,670
I intend to clearly expose
your wrongdoings.

192
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:00,320
That's unfair.

193
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:05,340
Our Get-Marriage has the number one
success rate in the matchmaking industry.

194
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:08,800
We have extremely high rates
of customer satisfaction.

195
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:13,530
We have introduced many
partners to Yukawa-sama.

196
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:16,480
Every one of them had
outstanding personal backgrounds.

197
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:19,380
But, I haven't found a partner.

198
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:22,490
Are you hiring planted fakes to keep
collecting membership dues?

199
00:09:22,490 --> 00:09:25,250
Our company would never
do anything like that.

200
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:28,470
The law is very strict
about such things.

201
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:32,860
Also, Yukawa-sama has
not been satisfied,

202
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:36,030
so we have repeatedly recommended
that she cancel her membership.

203
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,810
Is that so?

204
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:39,250
Well, yes...

205
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:42,290
If her dues were all that we wanted,
we wouldn't have done that.

206
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:47,880
We have done our utmost to satisfy
Yukawa-sama's demands.

207
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:51,660
But, as to why she cannot
find a partner...

208
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:54,070
well, the cause must lie elsewhere.

209
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:55,290
Just a second.

210
00:09:55,290 --> 00:09:58,280
You want to lay the
blame on Natsuko-san?

211
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,260
Kurumi-san, wait.

212
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:01,930
I never said that.

213
00:10:02,330 --> 00:10:05,000
I think Yukawa-sama is
a magnificent woman.

214
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,360
Let me ask you, Mr. Assistant.

215
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,190
Are you married?

216
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:11,370
No, not yet.

217
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:15,670
How does a person who's never been
married assist in matchmaking?

218
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:16,470
Right!

219
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:19,800
These men don't
understand women at all!

220
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,140
Yukawa-san, please—

221
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:23,360
Your necktie and shirt
combos are always

222
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,860
hideously mismatched!

223
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:26,880
Yellow necktie and blue shirt?

224
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,640
No sensibility!

225
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:31,920
And look at you, with
those smarmy rings.

226
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,890
Are you flaunting the money
you gouged from your members?

227
00:10:34,890 --> 00:10:36,320
Both of you, please calm down.

228
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,580
Kanae-san, take them outside.

229
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,170
Yes, let's go.

230
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:41,660
What? We didn't say anything wrong.

231
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:43,000
This way.

232
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,910
I find their comments offensive.

233
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:49,670
Perhaps I could counter
sue them for slander?

234
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:52,240
I apologize.

235
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:56,550
Well, I don't want matters
to get out of hand.

236
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,820
We will ask for Yukawa-sama
to cancel her membership,

237
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:03,450
and refund half of her membership fees.

238
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:04,950
Do we have a deal?

239
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:08,100
Please let me discuss it with her.

240
00:11:10,530 --> 00:11:12,030
Sir.

241
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,440
Do you think we're in the clear?

242
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:20,330
Get rid of our list.

243
00:11:20,970 --> 00:11:23,240
The "planted" list?

244
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,870
I wouldn't worry about it.

245
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:32,860
That lanky, frumpy lawyer doesn't
have the means to investigate us.

246
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,680
Hakamada Law Office

247
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,960
Half of all the dues I've paid?

248
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:40,900
I won't settle for that!

249
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,010
What's the point of
being your client,

250
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:45,460
if she was going to settle for that?

251
00:11:46,770 --> 00:11:50,160
Considering the circumstances,
I don't think that's a bad deal.

252
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,470
It's not like you to say
such things, Sensei.

253
00:11:52,470 --> 00:11:55,090
You're a compensation lawsuit
specialist, aren't you?

254
00:11:55,090 --> 00:11:58,660
As I said, I'm a divorce specialist.

255
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,320
Anyway, based on the current situation,

256
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:04,590
it would be difficult to
sue them for compensation.

257
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:06,010
Is that so?

258
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:06,670
No.

259
00:12:06,670 --> 00:12:07,850
Don't worry.

260
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:09,480
We'll do something about this.

261
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:12,540
Kurumi-san, please don't take
