information about me,

467
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:55,330
so he can find a completely
mismatched man for me!

468
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:57,160
That is entirely conceivable.

469
00:21:57,160 --> 00:22:00,310
But, Get-Marriage has
over a thousand members.

470
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:05,260
Would they go to such lengths
to scam a single member?

471
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:10,890
Maybe Tachibana-san has a personal
grudge against Natsuko-san.

472
00:22:10,890 --> 00:22:12,590
Against me?

473
00:22:12,590 --> 00:22:15,230
Can you think of some
reason why he would?

474
00:22:16,410 --> 00:22:17,660
No...

475
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:19,540
Not particularly.

476
00:22:21,390 --> 00:22:24,460
A reason why someone would have a
grudge against chief editor Yukawa?

477
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:25,460
Yes.

478
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:27,540
Misato-san, you're in the same office.

479
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:30,380
I thought you might know something.

480
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:33,880
Well... I can think of many reasons.

481
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,560
You know her personality.

482
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:37,100
She makes lots of enemies.

483
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:38,390
I see.

484
00:22:41,910 --> 00:22:42,960
Hello?

485
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:45,260
It's Kurumi. Have you found anything out?

486
00:22:45,260 --> 00:22:48,440
I've been speaking with
my editor about her.

487
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:49,490
I see.

488
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:52,230
I investigated Tachibana's history.

489
00:22:52,230 --> 00:22:56,440
That guy was proprietor of a ramen shop
before he landed the present job.

490
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:58,930
His shop went bust in less than a year,

491
00:22:58,930 --> 00:23:00,980
and he's been knee-deep in debt.

492
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:03,470
He's got debts from a ramen shop?

493
00:23:03,470 --> 00:23:05,030
A ramen shop?

494
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,780
Does that ring a bell?

495
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:10,030
Maybe his shop was featured in an
article in Yukawa's magazine.

496
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:13,940
There was a time they had an article
with scathing reviews of ramen shops.

497
00:23:13,940 --> 00:23:15,930
Maybe his shop got reviewed,

498
00:23:15,930 --> 00:23:18,630
and that's where his grudge came from.

499
00:23:18,630 --> 00:23:20,200
That's it!

500
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:23,010
I knew he had a personal grudge.

501
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:26,470
I'm going to go see Tachibana,
and nail him to the wall.

502
00:23:26,470 --> 00:23:30,040
Wait, before you do that, we should
get Hakamada-sensei's instructions...

503
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:32,510
We were warned by Get-Marriage, too...

504
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:36,070
This iron woman isn't
intimidated by warnings.

505
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:41,140
I feel it.

506
00:23:42,730 --> 00:23:43,920
What?

507
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:48,560
I feel a tremendous grudge the
man called Tachibana has against

508
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:51,090
the female chief editor.

509
00:23:51,090 --> 00:23:53,890
Yes, but we know that already.

510
00:24:00,250 --> 00:24:02,570
Can I talk to you for a minute?

511
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:06,770
Do you remember this?

512
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:12,690
It's got an article about
your ex-ramen shop.

513
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:14,950
Ramen,
Yeah Right!

514
00:24:10,330 --> 00:24:14,950
"Ramen Tachibana"

515
00:24:10,970 --> 00:24:14,950
Evaluation:
Materials
Noodles
Soup

516
00:24:12,690 --> 00:24:15,810
It's quite a harsh review.

517
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:20,470
Several months after the publication,
your establishment went under,

518
00:24:20,470 --> 00:24:23,570
and you were left with an enormous debt.

519
00:24:24,140 --> 00:24:27,040
You've had a grudge ever
since, haven't you?

520
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:30,180
Against Natsuki-san,
the author of the article.

521
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:32,900
That's not true!

522
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:36,770
My restaurant's business was
declining way before the article.

523
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:39,170
The article had nothing to do with it.

524
00:24:39,170 --> 00:24:42,230
My restaurant was destined to close.

525
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:47,030
You could say I'm actually thankful
to Yukawa-sama about that,

526
00:24:47,490 --> 00:24:50,220
because that article woke
me up to the hard facts.

527
00:24:50,220 --> 00:24:53,830
Then why are you obstructing
Natsuko-san's marriage interviews?

528
00:24:53,830 --> 00:24:58,090
I heard you spread bad rumors
about her to prospective partners.

529
00:25:00,170 --> 00:25:03,000
I'm not allowed to discuss
proprietary information.

530
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,260
Wait, you!

531
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:05,910
Please, leave me alone!

532
00:25:05,910 --> 00:25:08,270
Representative Ozaki is
stringent about rules.

533
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:09,910
If he found out I relayed
proprietary information,

534
00:25:09,910 --> 00:25:11,660
or that I got involved with a member,

535
00:25:11,660 --> 00:25:15,910
I'd be quickly fired, and
forced to pay 15 million yen.

536
00:25:15,910 --> 00:25:18,580
We know you've been following
Natsuko-san around!

537
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:25,080
What would you do if
that fact got publicized?

538
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:27,950
I think that's enough of that.

539
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:32,660
I warned you to stop
sniffing around us.

540
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,990
Who are you calling?

541
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,990
The police.

542
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:43,650
Your actions are no
different from blackmail.

543
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:49,680
I told you not to do reckless
investigations, did I not?!

544
00:25:51,070 --> 00:25:54,550
I got a serious warning
from the police.

545
00:25:54,990 --> 00:25:56,550
One more wrong move,

546
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:58,680
and you could have been arrested.

547
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:01,650
But, we need to find a way to win—

548
00:26:01,650 --> 00:26:05,490
Win or lose, that's my responsibility.

549
00:26:07,180 --> 00:26:08,930
Because of what happened,

550
00:26:08,930 --> 00:26:12,130
Get-Marriage will
tighten their security.

551
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:16,270
Now it will be harder than
ever to gather evidence.

552
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:23,320
You have worsened circumstances
considerably for our client.

553
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:28,630
Please cease your
involvement with this case.

554
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,860
Understood.

555
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,820
Um... here.

556
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:46,270
I recorded my conversation
with Tachibana.

557
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:48,670
I was hoping it might be of some use.

558
00:26:53,770 --> 00:26:55,670
Excuse me.

559
00:26:59,230 --> 00:27:02,410
Let's go out for drinks.
It's happy time.

560
00:27:02,410 --> 00:27:03,650
Marilyn.

561
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:05,970
Huh?

562
00:27:07,650 --> 00:27:09,020
Was there a fight?

563
00:27:09,020 --> 00:27:10,750
Yes. Somewhat.

564
00:27:16,690 --> 00:27:19,150
I see.

565
00:27:19,150 --> 00:27:21,230
Kurumi-chan overdid it.

566
00:27:21,230 --> 00:27:24,870
I've never seen
Hakamada-sensei get so angry.

567
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:31,890
She must've grown impatient with
Hakamada-sensei's procedures.

568
00:27:31,890 --> 00:27:33,340
What do you mean?

569
00:27:34,180 --> 00:27:40,120
There's more to the story
of Kurumi-chan's dissolved engagement.

570
00:27:42,650 --> 00:27:46,190
4 years ago

571
00:27:46,700 --> 00:27:50,530
Umemoto-san, time to
pay this month's rent.

572
00:27:50,530 --> 00:27:51,830
Ms. Landlord...

573
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:56,890
Are you still sniveling about that?

574
00:27:58,420 --> 00:28:02,460
I'll introduce you to
someone really nice.

575
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:03,600
Huh?

576
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:07,630
I understand the situation.

577
00:28:08,890 --> 00:28:10,980
Please leave the rest to me.

578
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:13,710
Oh. The rice is ready.

579
00:28:18,350 --> 00:28:19,800
Would you like to eat before you go?

580
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,290
It's freshly mixed rice.

581
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:22,960
Mixed rice?

582
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:24,930
At that time, Hakamada-sensei

583
00:28:24,930 --> 00:28:27,830
was into mixed rice, and not bread.

584
00:28:27,830 --> 00:28:29,710
Is that so?

585
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:32,830
And what Hakamada-sensei
did for her after that...

586
00:28:32,830 --> 00:28:34,850
was splendid.

587
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:43,330
In other words, you're saying
Umemoto-san is entirely at fault

588
00:28:43,330 --> 00:28:45,780
for the engagement dissolving, correct?

589
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:48,480
Of course.

590
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:51,690
How could I marry an
unsightly thing like that?

591
00:28:52,990 --> 00:28:54,860
I wonder if that's true.

592
00:29:01,050 --> 00:29:04,930
Here's evidence you were cheating
on her during your stint in Osaka.

593
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:09,840
I know I'm overstepping
my bounds, but...

594
00:29:10,810 --> 00:29:13,020
before you disparage
people's appearances,

595
00:29:13,020 --> 00:29:15,570
you ought to reflect
on your own actions.

596
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:21,620
We're suing for one million yen,
for breach of engagement.

597
00:29:22,250 --> 00:29:23,850
You will pay, won't you?

598
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:31,720
Umemoto-san, you were
lucky this time around.

599
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:32,920
Huh?

600
00:29:34,490 --> 00:29:38,610
Because you didn't wind
up marrying a cheater,

601
00:29:39,390 --> 00:29:41,460
who shallowly judges people
by their appearances.

602
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:58,900
Sensei.

603
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:02,690
What can I do for you?

604
00:30:02,690 --> 00:30:07,060
Will you please let Kurumi-san
continue her investigation?

605
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:11,740
I can't have her getting us
into any more trouble.

606
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:13,770
I heard from Yoshie-san.

607
00:30:14,390 --> 00:30:18,870
Kurumi-san was once your
client, wasn't she?

608
00:30:20,670 --> 00:30:22,970
She sure likes to gossip.

609
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:26,340
Kurumi-san put her
hopes in you, Sensei.

610
00:30:27,580 --> 00:30:29,440
She wanted you to save a client,

611
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:32,650
who suffered like she once did.

612
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:35,730
Maybe it's just me,

613
00:30:35,730 --> 00:30:38,610
but you're not yourself this
time around, Hakamada-sensei.

614
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:44,390
Maybe you got carried away
because you've been paired now,

615
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:46,360
but you should consider
your client's feelings,

616
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:48,960
consider her happiness.

617
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:51,040
Isn't that how you always work, Sensei?

618
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:58,930
Kurumi-san forced you to
take on this client...

619
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:02,450
because she believed in you.

620
00:31:04,610 --> 00:31:06,330
In that case, I wish

621
00:31:06,330 --> 00:31:08,920
she had kept believing in me,
just a little longer.

622
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,490
Huh?

623
00:31:10,490 --> 00:31:14,680
I haven't gotten carried away
in the least.

624
00:31:16,130 --> 00:31:19,510
The reason why I was
seeing my partner...

625
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:24,220
I see, so you wanted to investigate.

626
00:31:25,650 --> 00:31:27,310
I'm truly sorry.

627
00:31:27,310 --> 00:31:31,410
No, I'm glad you were honest with me.

628
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:36,010
I've gotten into relationships with
partners who stopped calling me,

629
00:31:36,010 --> 00:31:40,250
or reject me outright without
giving any reason whatsoever...

630
00:31:41,140 --> 00:31:42,550
Is that so?

631
00:31:43,180 --> 00:31:45,920
A friend of mine recommended
the company to me.

632
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,180
I've been a member for two years now.

633
00:31:48,180 --> 00:31:51,390
But, it ends the same
way every time.

634
00:31:52,170 --> 00:31:55,700
Would you mind sharing details with me?

635
00:31:55,700 --> 00:31:59,160
She gave me references to other members,

636
00:31:59,160 --> 00:32:01,140
and I spoke with several of them.

637
00:32:01,570 --> 00:32:03,060
Strangely enough,

638
00:32:03,060 --> 00:32:07,390
people's opinions of
Get-Marriage got split in two.

639
00:32:07,390 --> 00:32:09,690
Between those who are completely satisfied,

640
00:32:09,690 --> 00:32:10,910
and those who aren't.

641
00:32:10,910 --> 00:32:13,180
What's that mean?

642
00:32:13,180 --> 00:32:16,550
I think Get-Marriage sorts its members.

643
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,720
They're sorted into people
who will aggressively

644
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,920
get paired, in order to
raise their success rate...

645
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,750
and into people who are scammed,

646
00:32:23,750 --> 00:32:25,970
who only get set up with fakes.

647
00:32:25,970 --> 00:32:29,410
If you know that, you can
sue them for compensation.

648
00:32:29,410 --> 00:32:33,230
The only thing I'm missing
is solid evidence.

649
00:32:33,230 --> 00:32:34,770
However,

650
00:32:35,890 --> 00:32:39,270
thanks to this, I now
have a course of action.

651
00:32:39,270 --> 00:32:40,640
Huh?

652
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:43,060
Please call Kurumi-san for me.

653
00:32:43,060 --> 00:32:45,900
I need her to do further investigation.

654
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:47,380
Understood.

655
00:32:48,110 --> 00:32:51,780
Eternal Partners

656
00:32:52,310 --> 00:32:56,510
Have you agreed to our
terms from the other day?

657
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:57,850
No.

658
00:32:57,850 --> 00:33:01,350
We will be suing for a complete refund
of all membership fees paid,

659
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:03,790
as well as compensation.

660
00:33:03,790 --> 00:33:05,070
What?

661
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:06,930
Why have you decided that?

662
00:33:07,380 --> 00:33:14,130
Because you have purposefully obstructed
Natsuko-san from finding a marriage partner.

663
00:33:15,810 --> 00:33:19,920
And what advantage would we have
for doing something like that?

664
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:20,970
Well.

665
00:33:21,470 --> 00:33:25,590
You've been selecting targets.

666
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:31,220
You pick out people who
seem prone to rejection...

667
00:33:31,820 --> 00:33:34,790
and to keep raking membership
fees from those people,

668
00:33:34,790 --> 00:33:37,060
you obstruct them
from finding a mate.

669
00:33:38,150 --> 00:33:40,630
That's nonsense.

670
00:33:40,630 --> 00:33:42,170
You have no evidence.

671
00:33:42,170 --> 00:33:45,360
True, I don't have evidence.

672
00:33:45,360 --> 00:33:49,140
However, there is one thing we know.

673
00:33:50,170 --> 00:33:50,810
Tachibana-san.

674
00:33:51,980 --> 00:33:53,040
Yes.

675
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:58,350
You were obstructing Natsuko-san
for a personal reason, weren't you?

676
00:33:59,650 --> 00:34:01,950
This again?

677
00:34:01,950 --> 00:34:03,800
I don't have a grudge

678
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:06,580
against Yukawa-sama because
of that ramen shop article.

679
00:34:06,580 --> 00:34:07,760
No.

680
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:11,190
The personal reason isn't a grudge.

681
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:12,690
What?

682
00:34:12,690 --> 00:34:15,960
He is fond of Natsuko-san.

683
00:34:17,550 --> 00:34:19,030
Fond?

684
00:34:19,030 --> 00:34:20,880
The first time I noticed,

685
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:23,450
was when she commented
on your tie and shirt.

686
00:34:23,450 --> 00:34:25,840
Your necktie and shirt
combos are always

687
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,280
hideously mismatched!

688
00:34:27,280 --> 00:34:29,360
Yellow necktie and blue shirt?

689
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,150
No sensibility!

690
00:34:31,150 --> 00:34:34,180
A few days after Natsuko-san
criticized your color combinations,

691
00:34:34,180 --> 00:34:37,270
you took her words faithfully to heart.

692
00:34:37,270 --> 00:34:39,460
You changed the color of your tie.

693
00:34:43,420 --> 00:34:46,480
Because you are fond of Natsuko-san,

694
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:49,160
you wanted Natsuko-san for yourself...

695
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:52,370
so you were obstructing her prospects.

696
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:59,080
You can't infer all that
from the color of my tie.

697
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:01,300
That's no evidence of anything.

698
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:03,580
There's more evidence.

699
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,930
Hey, you, enough is enough.

700
00:35:08,930 --> 00:35:10,840
You had fair warning.

701
00:35:11,690 --> 00:35:14,200
I wasn't investigating you two.

702
00:35:14,650 --> 00:35:16,890
I found this site.

703
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:19,840
The author is anonymous,

704
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:20,830
Even if I only can talk with her
(Wednesday)
She came to our matchmaking firm again today.
She makes me happy, even speaking with her face to face. Even at my age, she makes my heart pound.

705
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:20,830
One-sided Confessions of a Matchmaking Firm

706
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:21,890
but it's blog by an employee
of a matchmaking firm,

707
00:35:20,830 --> 00:35:22,760
The joy of meeting with her

708
00:35:21,890 --> 00:35:25,040
confessing his secret love for a member.

709
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:24,530
A lovely bar

710
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,850
It talks about how he follows her home,

711
00:35:26,850 --> 00:35:30,020
and how he would get information
about her from people in her social circles.

712
00:35:30,020 --> 00:35:33,270
He's quite passionate about
her, as you can see.

713
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:32,500
A lovely bar

714
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:34,270
She's like an angel

715
00:35:33,270 --> 00:35:35,970
Oh yes, and have a look at this.

716
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:40,450
There's even a picture
of his secret love.

717
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:47,300
It would be easy to find the blogger.

718
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:51,410
This is ample evidence, wouldn't
you say, Hakamada-sensei?

719
00:35:51,810 --> 00:35:52,950
Yes.

720
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:56,090
I expect no less from you,
Investigator Umemoto.

721
00:35:59,620 --> 00:36:01,220
Tachibana-san.

722
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:04,240
Isn't it time to tell the truth?

723
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:08,370
Tachibana-san.

724
00:36:08,370 --> 00:36:10,260
I've had enough of you, Tachibana!

725
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:14,600
Who was it that got
you out of your debt?

726
00:36:16,110 --> 00:36:18,490
Have you forgotten the rules?

727
00:36:18,950 --> 00:36:22,690
Employees that leak proprietary
information will be penalized.

728
00:36:23,970 --> 00:36:26,450
Are you trying to get
yourself in debt again?

729
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:30,210
Is that the rule that would
force him to pay 15 million yen?

730
00:36:30,930 --> 00:36:33,710
He has exposed the illegal
activities of his company,

731
00:36:33,710 --> 00:36:36,960
and you would penalize him for that?

732
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:43,440
Public Well-Being Informant Protection Law

733
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:43,440
The law that protects workers who report unethical insider conduct

734
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:39,480
Based on the Public Well-Being
Informant Protection Law...

735
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,540
you can't do that.

736
00:36:47,210 --> 00:36:49,490
Shortly after I joined the company,

737
00:36:50,310 --> 00:36:55,310
representative Ozaki gave me a list.

738
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,220
The "planted" list...

739
00:37:01,060 --> 00:37:02,480
What this?

740
00:37:03,050 --> 00:37:08,600
It's a list of members who I believe
are unlikely to find a partner.

741
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:09,860
What?

742
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:13,010
Set them up with fake "plants,"

743
00:37:13,010 --> 00:37:15,920
and let them believe
they're getting somewhere.

744
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:19,890
People like that
desperately cling to us...

745
00:37:20,250 --> 00:37:24,610
and they'll keep paying
membership fees for all eternity.

746
00:37:26,580 --> 00:37:28,320
How awful.

747
00:37:29,070 --> 00:37:34,540
Yukawa-sama's name was
on that list, as well.

748
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:36,720
Yukawa Natsuko

749
00:37:37,610 --> 00:37:41,710
I thought I'd happened
upon an opportunity.

750
00:37:42,410 --> 00:37:44,330
Because as long as I was setting
her up with nothing but fakes,

751
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:46,770
I wouldn't have to worry about
Yukawa-sama ever getting married.

752
00:37:49,670 --> 00:37:52,230
It's true that I have
been obstructing her.

753
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:56,310
I thought maybe some day
she would go out with me.

754
00:37:56,310 --> 00:37:58,680
You shouldn't have been so devious.

755
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:02,190
Why didn't you just come out and
profess your love to Natsuko-san?

756
00:38:02,190 --> 00:38:04,890
Company rules prohibit relationships with members.

757
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:08,820
I was afraid of being penalized.

758
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:10,340
That's why...

759
00:38:10,740 --> 00:38:13,030
that why after Yukawa-sama resigned,

760
00:38:15,890 --> 00:38:19,430
I was going to properly ask her out.

761
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:29,150
So that's how it is.

762
00:38:29,750 --> 00:38:34,110
It's clear you've been scamming
your members using fakes.

763
00:38:35,450 --> 00:38:38,110
The total membership
fees and compensation...

764
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:39,560
You will pay, won't you?

765
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,210
And one more thing.

766
00:38:43,830 --> 00:38:44,990
Tachibana-san.

767
00:38:44,990 --> 00:38:49,630
Please inform all members on that list.

768
00:38:50,470 --> 00:38:52,330
Like Natsuko-san,

769
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:55,100
they have fallen victim to a scam.

770
00:38:59,190 --> 00:39:01,370
If you do that, our company will be ruined!

771
00:39:01,370 --> 00:39:03,840
And what's wrong with that?

772
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:07,330
After all, you shallowly judge
people based on appearances...

773
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:10,720
You're not qualified to
oversee human encounters.

774
00:39:16,190 --> 00:39:19,680
Umemoto-san, you were
lucky this time around.

775
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:23,660
Because you didn't wind
up marrying a cheater,

776
00:39:24,580 --> 00:39:26,930
who shallowly judges people
by their appearances.

777
00:39:36,490 --> 00:39:39,890
You look like an
insignificant lawyer...

778
00:39:41,490 --> 00:39:45,730
but I guess you can't judge
people on appearances.

779
00:39:59,260 --> 00:40:02,600
Hakamada Law Office

780
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:07,700
Major corporation Get-Marriage crushed
Illicit activities toward its members uncovered

781
00:40:03,050 --> 00:40:06,620
Wow, the matchmaking firm
went out of business.

782
00:40:06,620 --> 00:40:08,940
That's our Hakamada-sensei.

783
00:40:08,940 --> 00:40:12,190
He rescued not one, but many people.

784
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:18,010
I am truly sorry about how
I behaved this time around.

785
00:40:18,770 --> 00:40:20,280
If you are,

786
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:23,000
then please do not do reckless
investigations any more.

787
00:40:23,740 --> 00:40:25,190
I understand.

788
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:28,530
Sensei, we have a guest.

789
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:29,730
Yes.

790
00:40:31,910 --> 00:40:33,600
Natsuko-san.

791
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:37,000
Thank you for everything
you have done for me.

792
00:40:37,650 --> 00:40:38,970
You too, dear.

793
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:46,940
Everyone. I have caused
you much trouble.

794
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:48,420
Tachibana-san.

795
00:40:48,420 --> 00:40:49,510
Why are you here, too?

796
00:40:50,450 --> 00:40:54,880
Well, we are getting married.

797
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:55,990
What?

798
00:40:55,990 --> 00:40:59,590
That day, when Tachibana-san
confessed his feelings,

799
00:40:59,590 --> 00:41:01,690
I couldn't get that out of my mind.

800
00:41:01,690 --> 00:41:04,860
So I got brave, and called him.

801
00:41:06,690 --> 00:41:09,220
I brought hardship to many people.

802
00:41:09,220 --> 00:41:12,530
For that, I must make amends
for the rest of my life.

803
00:41:13,450 --> 00:41:18,390
But, Natsuko-san forgave me.

804
00:41:19,570 --> 00:41:24,050
I will make her happy, I promise!

805
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,530
I'm glad for you.

806
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:38,030
The compensation we received
will help us make a new start.

807
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:40,820
We cannot thank Sensei enough.

808
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:46,120
If you're going to show gratitude...

809
00:41:47,700 --> 00:41:49,780
it should be toward her.

810
00:41:49,780 --> 00:41:50,700
Huh?

811
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:54,450
We couldn't have sued for compensation

812
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:56,770
without her investigation.

813
00:42:03,420 --> 00:42:08,350
Speaking of which, here is the bill
for the case's investigation.

814
00:42:09,290 --> 00:42:11,470
Can you please wait a little for that?

815
00:42:11,470 --> 00:42:12,890
You said you couldn't have sued for

816
00:42:12,890 --> 00:42:15,260
compensation if it weren't
for my investigation, right?

817
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:17,420
That and this are unrelated...

818
00:42:17,420 --> 00:42:19,230
Wait! Grab him!

819
00:42:19,230 --> 00:42:20,400
Please, don't do this!

820
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,670
I will pay it.

821
00:42:22,670 --> 00:42:24,700
I promise I'll pay it!

822
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:27,410
You're taking the children
away from me, too?

823
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:36,080
Next episode

824
00:42:27,410 --> 00:42:29,410
He's a pathetic husband
who can't find another job.

825
00:42:27,470 --> 00:42:31,610
Childcare worker husband VS career-woman wife

826
00:42:29,410 --> 00:42:31,240
So I threatened
him with a knife.

827
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:32,880
The wife admits
to illicit activity.

828
00:42:31,610 --> 00:42:36,080
A mess of a custody battle:
What will happen to the children's future?!

829
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:34,200
In which case we can
sue for compensation.

830
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:36,080
You're not a
superhero of justice!

831
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:39,680
You're a villain that's
splitting Mama and Papa apart!

832
00:42:36,250 --> 00:42:39,720
This drama is a work of fiction

